    <text type="letter"> 
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.01292_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener> 
                <dateline> 
                    <name type="place">Walt Whitman Esq.</name>
                    <name type="place"><hi rend="underline">Phila<ptr target="loc.04859_n1"/></hi></name>
                    <date when="1892-01-17">Jan 17<hi rend="underline">th</hi></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friend&#8212;</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Just as I was deeply interested in reading "John Russell Youngs<ptr target="n0737a"/> reminiscences of 
                <hi rend="underline">Walt Whitman</hi>" as published in last 
                evn'gs Paper, my soul enters with the pleasing tidings that you 
                were not "only <hi rend="underline">sitting up</hi>" (in bed) 
                but was partaking with a <hi rend="underline">relish</hi> of such food 
                as you had not till now
                been allowed or <hi rend="underline">desired</hi>." To 
                gain <hi rend="underline">strength</hi> is what you need to 
                combat with your disease &#38; <hi rend="underline">nourishing</hi> 
                food may bring about this happy result.</p>
            <p>Such we shall pray &#38;<pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.01293_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                hope for&#8212;I have always longed to hear you recite 
                "Captain, Oh, My Captain,"<ptr target="loc.04859_n3"/> &#38; 
                <hi rend="underline">may I not yet hear it</hi>?</p>
            <p>I would again come over to see you, but I am not myself well &#38; <hi rend="underline">you</hi>
                are too sick to entertain even friends.</p>
            <p>To our Heavenly Fathers care I consign you, dear friend, 
                trusting He will spare you to us yet a little longer.  
            </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Truly Yours</salute>
                <signed>Lavinia F. Whitman</signed> 
                <address>
                    <addrLine>Phila, 2337 N. 18th</addrLine>
                </address>
            </closer>
